        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-24T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-24T02:00:00-05:00" n="758" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/10–2448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-24T15:00:00+08:00">October 24, 1948—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 24—5:46 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1984. With reference Deptel 1484, October 23, repeated Peiping 188 and Tientsin
                    197, we feel Embtel October 23 sent Peiping 189 and Tientsin 173; repeated
                    Department 1980 adequately meets situation. Sent Department 1984, repeated
                    Peiping 192, Tientsin 175.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
